[3] H5N1, Stone marten: environmental impact
Date: Fri, 10 Mar 2006
From: Mark Pokras <mark.pokras@tufts.edu>

Mustelids and influenza
-----------------------
Domestic ferrets are well-known to be extremely
sensitive to human influenza viruses both as pets
and in laboratory settings.
I wonder what effects this may have on
populations of small mammalian predators and the
potential for subsequent population explosions of
rodents (and their pathogens) in the next year or
two?
--
Mark A. Pokras, DVM
Director, Center for Conservation Medicine
Tufts University
Cummings School of Veterinary Medicine
N. Grafton, MA, USA 01536
<mark.pokras@tufts.edu>
